2007-05-22	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-05-21	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-05-17	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-05-16	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-05-15	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* BP2-MacOS.cw8.mcp:
		Added dlgxs.rsrc to Carbon builds (but not Transitional builds).
	
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (Answer & Alert1):
		Don't call MainEvent() with AlertOn from here, because it prevents
			the reactivation of dialogs.  (#if !EXPERIMENTAL for now)
	
	* source/BP2/Strings.c (TooLongFileName):  Don't Strip() filenames.
	
	* source/BP2/MIDIloads.c (LoadTimePattern):
		Made sure pattern duration not set to 0 in dialog and that the values
			are retrieved from edit texts after dismissing dialog so that
			it does not erroneously report "bad characters".
		Changed BringToFront() to SelectWindow().
		
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (AnswerWith):
		Replaced custom event loop with ModalDialog() call.
		Changed BringToFront() to SelectWindow().
	
	* source/prefix/PrefixTransTextEdit.h:
	* source/prefix/PrefixTransWASTE.h:
		Added #define USE_OLD_EDIT_TEXT 1 for pre-OS 8 edit text boxes.

	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (SetField):
		Use GetDialogItemAsControl() instead of GetDialogItem() when building
			with Appearance-compliant static & edit text controls.  Fixes
			the text not updating sometimes.  (#if !USE_OLD_EDIT_TEXT).
		Don't change text selection or deactivate the dialog's TE handle.
	
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (AnswerWith, SetFindReplace):
	* source/BP2/MIDIloads.c (LoadTimePattern):
	* source/BP2/Misc.c (SetTempo, SetBufferSize, SetGraphicsSettings, 
						 SetTimeAccuracy, SetKeyboard, & SetSeed):
	* source/BP2/Ticks.c (SetTimeBase):
		Replace direct calls to SetDialogItemText() with our SetField()
			instead (propagating the fix for text controls).
		Remove erroneous calls to TESetSelect().
		
	* resources/dlgxs.rsrc:
		New file with dlgx resources. Most dialogs now have Appearance Mngr.
		features including automatically setting the theme background, 
		creating an embedding hierarchy, and making all dialog items real 
		controls.  These features improve the edit text boxes and cause
		controls to be automagically activated and deactivated with the 
		window.  Exceptions in our dlgx's include not creating embedding
		hierarchy for "floating" dialogs so that they will not be deactivated
		and not using theme background for Prototype7 and Csound Tables.
	  
	* source/BP2/BP2main.c (main):
	* source/BP2/AppleEvents.c (DoHighLevelEvent, GoodEvent, MyHandleOAPP):
		Made GoodEvent() always return YES so that all Apple events are passed
			to system handler.  This fixes incompatibility with Default Folder.
		Suppressed unhandled event error reporting and fixed OAPP event.

	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/Inits.c (Inits):
		Reversed semantics of FirstTimeAE and renamed it ReceivedOpenAppEvent.

	* source/BP2/CoreMIDIdriver.c (CreateCMSettings):  Set keyboard focus.
	* resources/CoreMIDISettings.rsrc:  Added dlgx #1000 resource.
	
	* BP2 help:
		Updated "Types-creators" and "Where can I get the latest version..."
	 
2007-05-12	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
		New global WindowUsesThemeBkgd[WMAX] for choosing whether windows get
			the default dialog background ("pin-stripped" on OS X).
			
	* source/BP2/-BP2.proto.h:
	* source/BP2/Dialogs.c (BPSetDialogAppearance):
	* source/BP2/Inits.c (MakeWindows):
		BPSetDialogAppearance() takes an extra parameter controlling whether
			the dialog gets painted with the default background.
		MakeWindows() modified so that all dialogs with edit text boxes do
			not use the default background.

2007-05-11	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c (NewFile & OldFile):
		Removed #ifdefs for Carbon and Standard File Package code so that 
			NavServWrapper code is always used in all builds.
	
	* source/BP2/NavServWrapper.c (NSWGetFile & NSWPutFile):
		Finished the backwards-compatible support for using StdFilePkg
			when Nav Serv. is not available. (non-Carbon only)
	
	* source/prefix/PrefixTransWASTE.h:
		#defines for turning off unneeded WASTE features.

