2007-05-01	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/Inits.c:
	* source/BP2/Interface1.c (ClearWindow):
	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c (CheckTextSize):
	* source/BP2/WindowText.c (TextInsert & DoKey):
		Further revisions to keep from overflowing TextEdit buffer and so
			that BP2 only reports the error once (until not full again). 

	* BP2-MacOS.cw8.mcp:
		New target for building MachO binary with WASTE.
		Removed WEDebug.c, WEObjectHandlers.c, WEObjects.c, WETabHooks.c, 
			and WETabs.c from all WASTE targets as they are not used.
	
	* source/prefix/PrefixCarbonWASTE.h:  Turned off unused WASTE features.
	
	* source/prefix/PrefixMachOWASTE.h:  New prefix file.

	* source/WASTE/WASTE.h:
	* source/WASTE/WASTEIntf.h:
	* source/WASTE/WEArrays.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEBirthDeath.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEDebug.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEDrawing.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEHighLevelEditing.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEInlineInput.c:
	* source/WASTE/WELineLayout.c:
	* source/WASTE/WELongCoords.c:
	* source/WASTE/WELowLevelEditing.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEMouse.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEObjects.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEScraps.c:
	* source/WASTE/WESelecting.c:
	* source/WASTE/WESelectors.c:
	* source/WASTE/WEUtilities.c:
		Carbonized the portions of WASTE that BP2 is using.

	* source/BP2/MenuCommands.c (mGlossary):
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (SetOptionMenu & Replace):
		Change 'Glossary' item to 'Tokenized Glossary' with Option key.
		Alert user when replacement fails.  (Redundant error message?)
	
	* source/BP2/Interface1.c (BPActivateWindow):
		EXPERIMENTAL-ly removed two lines: ShowSelect() when activating
			window (WASTE-only); UpdateWindow() (!WASTE).  The latter
			of these was causing static/edit text in wPrototypes1 to not
			be redrawn sometimes? (and it seems otherwise unnecessary)

	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c:
		Changed "Netscape HTML" to "Standard HTML" in Save format menu.
		Use creator type '\0\0\0\0' on OS X for HTML files.

	* source/BP2/ProduceItems.c (ProduceItems):
		Don't mark Start String window as Dirty when inserting "S".
	
2007-04-30	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* resources/BP2-MacOS.rsrc (DLOG #535 & #536):
	* source/BP2/Inits.c (MakeWindows):
		Resize Top & Bottom Settings windows and adjust Buttonheight to 18
			while creating them on OS X.

	* source/BP2/-BP2.h:
	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c (CheckTextSize):
	* source/BP2/WindowText.c (DoKey & TextPaste):
		#define TEXTEDIT_MAXCHARS 32000L char limit in TextEdit windows.
		(while TextEdit does not crash until > 32767 chars are in the TERec,
		  there appears to be an implied limit of 32000 chars in TextEdit.h?) 
		DoKey(), TextPaste() check if limit would be exceeded.
		CheckTextSize() checks if TERec length is < 0, indicating overflow.

2007-04-27	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* resources/ClassicDialogs.rsrc:
		New resource file with the old color tables and dialog layouts for
			the non-Carbon build.  Also includes the rounded-corner "desk
			accessory" DLOG resources -- these are incompatible with OS X.

	* resources/BP2-MacOS.rsrc (DLOG #546, DITL #643 & #650):
