		Enlarged the Cancel and arrow buttons of the dynamic button dialogs.
		Check the return value of TrackControl for a positive "hit".
	
2007-04-26	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/Inits.c (GoodMachine):
		Check for Appearance Manager and set new global HaveAppearanceManager.

	* source/BP2/-BP2.proto.h:
	* source/BP2/Inits.c (SetUpMenus):
	* source/BP2/Interface1.c (DoEvent):
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (SetOptionMenu):
		Moved code for help key shortcuts to new function DoHelpKey().
		When the Appearance Mgr is available, SetUpMenus() and SetOptionMenu()
			now use it to set the keyboard equivalents for menu items with
			option-key shortcuts (without changing the menu item text). 
		Moved code for handling Command-key shortcuts to new functions
			DoKeyCommand() & DoPreMacOS8KeyCommand().  The latter handles
			option-key combinations without the Appearance Mgr.
			DoKeyCommand() first filters non-menu commands then uses
			MenuEvent() if Appearance Mgr is available so that all Roman-
			script keyboard layouts work correctly with option-key shortcuts.

2007-04-25	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/Dialogs.c (DoDialog):
	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (CantOpen):
		Call QDFlushPortBuffer() so that button hiliting changes in the MIDI 
			Channel and Program Change dialogs before testing output.  Also, 
			so that the message in CantOpen() is drawn.
 
2007-04-24	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* resources/BP2-MacOS.rsrc:
		Resized buttons and respaced layouts for the Control Panel, Script
			Dialog, MIDI channel ("Sixteen"), Time Accuracy, and File Save 
