2007-04-20	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/-BP2.proto.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/Interface1.c (DoEvent & MaintainMenus):
	* source/BP2/MenuCommands.c (mPlaySelectionOrPrototype):
		Don't use Command-space to play the current sound-object on OS X.
		When any of the prototypes windows are active, the 'Play selection'
			menu item (but not the button on the Control Panel) changes to
			'Play sound-object' and is enabled if there is a current object.
		Choosing this item or pressing Cmd-P will call the new function 
			mPlaySelectionOrPrototype() that determines the context and then
			plays either the current sound-object or the text selection within 
			the last active edit window. (Usual problems with Nw apply).

2007-04-19	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/Interface2.c (ShowMessage & FlashInfo):
		Use SendBehind(FrontWindow()) instead of BringToFront() on OS X
			because the latter sometimes activates the window.

