2007-04-12	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-04-11	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>
2007-04-10	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/Misc.c:
		Fixed bug in SetButtons() that turned off OutMIDI before driver inits.
		Fixed bug in Date() that returned corrupted time string.
		
	* resources/BP2-MacOS.rsrc:
		Changed version resource's country code to "U.S.".
		Made sure window and dialog positions are below menu bar.
		 
	* source/BP2/BP2main.c:
	* source/BP2/Script.c:
		Replaced calls to RunScriptOnDisk() for +sc.startup and +sc.shutdown
			with new function RunScriptInPrefsOrAppFolder().
		RunScriptInPrefsOrAppFolder() encapsulates all of the setup for 
			running and now searches for special scripts in the user or 
			system preferences folder (or BP's folder if not found).
		Fixed bug with EventState that prevented shutdown script from running.
		
	* source/BP2/-BP2.proto.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/ScriptUtils.c:
		Corrections where int was used instead of short for vRefNums.
		
	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c (MyOpen):  Return correct error codes.

	* source/BP2/MenuCommands.c:
	* source/BP2/Script.c:
		Make sure error messages are not hidden when saving a file.
		Changes to make sure that Created[w] is maintained when checking
			or executing a script.
	
	* source/BP2/-BP2.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2.proto.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2decl.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
	* source/BP2/BP2main.c:
	* source/BP2/MIDIfiles.c:
	* source/BP2/ProduceItems.c:
	* source/BP2/SaveLoads3.c:
	* source/BP2/Script.c:
		CreateTemporaryFile() now uses system Temp folder and returns FSSpec.
		OpenTemp() saves spec to new global TempSpec.
		New constants for temp file names: kBPTempFile, kBPTraceFile.
		Moved code for removing BP2.temp from ProduceItems.c to 
			CloseAndDeleteTemp() in SaveLoads3.c
		New func CloseFileAndUpdateVolume() for closing temps that 
			retrieves the vRefNum and flushes the volume.
		Close BP2.temp & BP2.trace with CloseFileAndUpdateVolume() in main().
		Replaced BP's FlushVolume() with File Mngr's FlushVol() and made
			other changes so that we are always flushing the correct volume.

