	* source/BP2/Script.c:
	* source/BP2/ScriptUtils.c:
		Initial support for Multilingual Text Engine.
		TextHandle typedef is defined as our own record with MLTE.
		SetUpWindow() creates MLTE objects to associate with text windows.
		Replaced all accesses of TextEdit/WASTE record fields with calls
			to new functions TextGetViewRect(), TextIsSelectionEmpty(), and
			TextGetSelection().
		Conditionalized some of the code in WindowText.c and some of the
			event handling in Interface1.c to make equivalent MLTE calls.
		
2007-04-04	Bernard Bel	<bel@lpl.univ-aix.fr>
(Commited by Anthony)

	* source/BP2/Compute.c:
		Call ReleaseProduceStackSpace() and reset MaxDeriv at the beginning of
			Compute() to avoid allocating too much memory in 
			IncreaseComputeSpace().
		Changes to ComputeInGram() so that Repeat Production does not perform
			an extra step (rule weight was not being decreased in last step).
	
	* source/BP2/FillPhaseDiagram.c (FillPhaseDiagram):
		Round the value of maxseqapprox up with ceil().

2007-04-03	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* scripts/+sc.checkall:
		Uncommented grammars that were causing errors in FillPhaseDiagram.

2007-04-03	Bernard Bel	<bel@lpl.univ-aix.fr>
(Commited by Anthony)

	* source/BP2/GetRelease.c (ReleaseObjectPrototypes):
		Set (*p_MIDIsize)[j] to 0 when disposing of (*pp_MIDIcode)[j] handles.
	
	* source/BP2/Interface1.c (ClearWindow):
		Don't call ReleaseObjectPrototypes() from ClearWindow(); fixes crash.

	* source/BP2/FillPhaseDiagram.c (Class & FillPhaseDiagram):
		Rounded the calculation in Class() to avoid errors.
		Redeclared **p_currobject, **p_objectsfound, objectsfound as double.
		Removed unused variables throughout this file.

2007-04-02	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/BP2main.c:
		Revised memory management scheme when running on OS X:
		 No longer uses FreeMem() or MaxMem() since they are inaccurate.
		 No longer uses temporary memory functions since they are no different
			than "regular memory" on OS X.
		 Does not keep a reserve of "emergency memory" on OS X.
		 Gives up immediately if an allocation fails on OS X but does not set
		 	EmergencyExit.  (Perhaps this could be improved).
		 Might be a good idea to stop and warn the user when total allocations
		 	are nearly equal to the size of physical memory (to prevent a
		 	massive slowdown when using too much virtual memory).
	
	* source/BP2/Inits.c:
		Do not allocate space for h_EmergencyMemory on OS X.

2007-03-28	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/Dialogs.c (BPSetDialogAppearance):
		Fix for non-Carbon builds.
	
	* BP2-MacOS.cw8.mcp:  Weak link NavigationLib & other non-required libs.
	
2007-03-27	Anthony Kozar	<anthonykozar@sbcglobal.net>

	* source/BP2/BP2main.c:
		Changed reporting of memory leaks to depend on TraceMemory instead of
			CheckMem since TraceMemory can be controlled by BIGTEST macro.
	
	* source/BP2/-BP2.h:
	* source/BP2/-BP2main.h:
		Added "BP2.9.6beta" to VersionName[] and updated Version, IDSTRING, 
			MAXVERSION, and VERSIONLENGTH.
	
	* resources/BP2-MacOS.rsrc:
		Added myself to developers in the about box.
		Added mapping for Data icon to type 'TEXT' in BNDL resource.

	* Credits.txt:  Added note about Carbon porting.

